{"description":"The following code make the semantic analysis fail for the whole file.\r\n{code}\r\npublic void foo() {\r\n  try {\r\n    doSomething();\r\n  } catch (SQLException | IOException e) {  // fail type resolution\r\n    // do somehting else\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe exception {{SQLException}} extends {{java.lang.Exception}}, but also implements {{Iterable\u003cThrowable\u003e}}.\r\n\r\nHowever, the current calculation of the *least upper bound* for union types throws an {{IllegalArgumentException}} when detecting a parametrized type in the hierarchy, failing the type resolution and thus the semantic analysis.","component":"SonarJava","component_version":"3.9"}